Australian dies in PNG plane crash
A Sydney ship pilot and three other people are believed to have died in a plane crash in Papua New Guinea's Milne Bay Province.
Australian Reef Pilots have confirmed that one of their Australian marine pilots, who was on his way to guide a ship through the Great Barrier Reef, had died when the chartered plane crashed on Tuesday afternoon.
The plane's pilot is believed to have been the only survivor of the crash and was reported to be in a critical condition in the local hospital.
The New Zealand High Commission in PNG confirmed two New Zealanders were aboard the flight.
Australian Reef Pilots (ARP) on Tuesday night released a statement confirming one of their marine pilots died in the crash.
ARP managing Director Craig Southerwood said he was a 61-year-old Sydney resident.